README
=================

First setup with:

TEMPLATECONF=meta-elk/conf source oe-init-build-env build-elk


Then build your image with:

bitbake elk-core-image-sato


Bootable images can be found inside:

build-elk/tmp/deploy/images/up-board-elk

Available images
.iso: live read-only iso
.hddimg: bootable image (rootfs is a single file .img file mounted in readwrite at boot)
.wic: "classic" disc image with a complete rootfs, ready to be dd-ed on the USB key


Layer Depends on meta-openembedded layer https://github.com/openembedded/meta-openembedded branch: rocko  
